<h2 class=3D"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id=3D"jans-principles">Jan=
=E2=80=99s principles<a href=3D"https://jan.ai/about/#jans-principles" clas=
s=3D"hash-link" aria-label=3D"Direct link to Jan=E2=80=99s principles" titl=
e=3D"Direct link to Jan=E2=80=99s principles">=E2=80=8B</a></h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ownership</strong>: Jan is committed to developing a product th=
at fully belongs to users. You're the true owner, free from data tracking a=
nd storage by us.</li>
<li><strong>Privacy</strong>: Jan works locally by default, allowing use wi=
thout an internet connection. Your data stays on your device in a universal=
 format, giving you complete privacy control.</li>
<li><strong>100% User Supported</strong>: Every user can access, develop, a=
nd customize Jan's codebases to suit their needs.</li>
<li><strong>Rejecting Dark Patterns</strong>: We never use tricks to extrac=
t more money or lock you into an ecosystem.</li>
</ul>
<h2 class=3D"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id=3D"why-do-we-exist">Why=
 do we exist?<a href=3D"https://jan.ai/about/#why-do-we-exist" class=3D"has=
h-link" aria-label=3D"Direct link to Why do we exist?" title=3D"Direct link=
 to Why do we exist?">=E2=80=8B</a></h2>
<blockquote>
<p><em>"I do not fear computers. I fear the lack of them." - Isaac Asimov</=
em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Jan was founded on the belief that AI should coexist with humans, not re=
place them. Our mission is to democratize AI access, ensuring everyone can =
easily utilize it with full ownership and control over their data, free fro=
m privacy concerns.</p>
<h3 class=3D"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id=3D"what-are-the-things-=
jan-committed-on">What are the things Jan committed on?<a href=3D"https://j=
an.ai/about/#what-are-the-things-jan-committed-on" class=3D"hash-link" aria=
-label=3D"Direct link to What are the things Jan committed on?" title=3D"Di=
rect link to What are the things Jan committed on?">=E2=80=8B</a></h3>
<p>We are committed to creating open, local-first products that extend indi=
vidual freedom, rejecting dark patterns and ecosystem lock-ins, and embraci=
ng an open-source ethos.</p>
<h4 class=3D"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id=3D"whats-different-abou=
t-it">What's different about it?<a href=3D"https://jan.ai/about/#whats-diff=
erent-about-it" class=3D"hash-link" aria-label=3D"Direct link to What's dif=
ferent about it?" title=3D"Direct link to What's different about it?">=E2=
=80=8B</a></h4>
<table><thead><tr><th></th><th>Status Quo</th><th>Jan</th></tr></thead><tbo=
dy><tr><td><strong>Ownership</strong></td><td>Owned by Big Tech</td><td>Ful=
ly owned by you</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Openness</strong></td><td>Closed-s=
ource</td><td><a href=3D"https://github.com/janhq/jan/blob/main/LICENSE" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Open-source (AGPLv3)</a></td></=
tr><tr><td><strong>Your Role</strong></td><td>Consumer</td><td>Creator</td>=
</tr><tr><td><strong>Approach</strong></td><td>Cloud-based</td><td><a href=
=3D"https://www.inkandswitch.com/local-first/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noo=
pener noreferrer">Local-first</a></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Data Handling</s=
trong></td><td>Stored on external servers</td><td>Stored locally, openly ac=
cessible</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Privacy</strong></td><td>Questionable</td=
><td>Private and offline</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Transparency</strong></td=
><td>Opaque "Black Box"</td><td>Open-source and customizable</td></tr><tr><=
td><strong>Outage Resilience</strong></td><td>Potential data hostage</td><t=
d>Continues to work on your device</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Philosophy</str=
ong></td><td>User monetization</td><td>Empowerment with the right to repair=
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<h2 class=3D"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id=3D"how-we-work">How we =
work<a href=3D"https://jan.ai/about/#how-we-work" class=3D"hash-link" aria-=
label=3D"Direct link to How we work" title=3D"Direct link to How we work">=
=E2=80=8B</a></h2>
<p>Jan is an open-source product with transparent development and future fe=
atures. Users have the right to modify and customize Jan. We are committed =
to building an open-source AI ecosystem.</p>
<p>Jan is building in public using GitHub, where anyone is welcome to join.=
 Key resources include Jan's <a href=3D"https://github.com/orgs/janhq/proje=
cts/5/views/7" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Kanban</a> and=
 Jan's <a href=3D"https://github.com/orgs/janhq/projects/5/views/29" target=
=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Roadmap</a>.</p>
<p>Jan has a fully-remote team, primarily based in the APAC timezone, and w=
e use Discord and GitHub for collaboration. Our community is central to our=
 operations, and we embrace asynchronous work. We hold meetings only for sy=
nchronization and vision sharing, using <a href=3D"https://excalidraw.com/"=
 target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Excalidraw</a> or <a href=3D=
"https://miro.com/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Miro</a> =
for visualization and sharing notes on Discord for alignment. We also use <=
a href=3D"https://hackmd.io/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer"=
>HackMD</a> to document our ideas and build a Jan library.</p>
<h2 class=3D"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id=3D"how-to-get-it">How t=
o get it?<a href=3D"https://jan.ai/about/#how-to-get-it" class=3D"hash-link=
" aria-label=3D"Direct link to How to get it?" title=3D"Direct link to How =
to get it?">=E2=80=8B</a></h2>
<p>You can install and start using Jan in less than 5 minutes, from <a href=
=3D"https://jan.ai/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Jan.ai</=
a> or our <a href=3D"https://github.com/janhq/jan" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D=
"noopener noreferrer">Github repo</a>.</p>
<h2 class=3D"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id=3D"what-license-is-the-=
code-under">What license is the code under?<a href=3D"https://jan.ai/about/=
#what-license-is-the-code-under" class=3D"hash-link" aria-label=3D"Direct l=
ink to What license is the code under?" title=3D"Direct link to What licens=
e is the code under?">=E2=80=8B</a></h2>
<p>Jan is licensed under the <a href=3D"https://github.com/janhq/jan/blob/m=
ain/LICENSE" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">AGPLv3 License</=
a>.</p>
<p>We happily accept pull requests, however, we do ask that you sign a <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contributor_License_Agreement" target=
=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Contributor License Agreement</a> s=
o that we have the right to relicense your contributions<sup><a href=3D"htt=
ps://jan.ai/about/#user-content-fn-2" id=3D"user-content-fnref-2" data-foot=
note-ref=3D"true" aria-describedby=3D"footnote-label">1</a></sup>.</p>
<h2 class=3D"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id=3D"what-was-it-built-wi=
th">What was it built with?<a href=3D"https://jan.ai/about/#what-was-it-bui=
lt-with" class=3D"hash-link" aria-label=3D"Direct link to What was it built=
 with?" title=3D"Direct link to What was it built with?">=E2=80=8B</a></h2>
<p><a href=3D"https://github.com/janhq/jan" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopen=
er noreferrer">Jan</a> is pragmatically built using <code>Typescript</code>=
 at the application level and <code>C++</code> at the Inference level (whic=
h we have refactored into <a href=3D"https://nitro.jan.ai/" target=3D"_blan=
k" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Nitro</a><sup><a href=3D"https://jan.ai/abou=
t/#user-content-fn-3" id=3D"user-content-fnref-3" data-footnote-ref=3D"true=
" aria-describedby=3D"footnote-label">2</a></sup>).</p>
<p>We follow <a href=3D"https://blog.cleancoder.com/uncle-bob/2012/08/13/th=
e-clean-architecture.html" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">cl=
ean architecture</a> and currently support multiple frameworks and runtimes=
:</p>
<ul>
<li>A desktop client with <a href=3D"https://www.electronjs.org/" target=3D=
"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Electron</a></li>
<li>A headless server-mode with <a href=3D"https://nodejs.org/en" target=3D=
"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Nodejs</a></li>
<li>Planned support for mobile with <a href=3D"https://capacitorjs.com/" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Capacitor</a></li>
<li>Planned support for Python runtime</li>
</ul>
<p>Architecturally, we have made similar choices to the <a href=3D"https://=
vercel.com/templates/next.js/nextjs-enterprise-boilerplate" target=3D"_blan=
k" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Next.js Enterprise Javascript Stack</a>, whi=
ch is a <a href=3D"https://nextjs.org/showcase/enterprise" target=3D"_blank=
" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">battle-tested</a> framework for building ente=
rprise-grade applications that scale.</p>
<h2 class=3D"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id=3D"join-the-team">Join =
the team<a href=3D"https://jan.ai/about/#join-the-team" class=3D"hash-link"=
 aria-label=3D"Direct link to Join the team" title=3D"Direct link to Join t=
he team">=E2=80=8B</a></h2>
<p>Join us on this journey at Jan Labs, where we embrace open-source collab=
oration and transparency. Together, let's shape a future where Jan becomes =
an essential companion in the open-source community. Explore <a href=3D"htt=
ps://janai.bamboohr.com/careers" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferr=
er">careers</a> with us.</p>
<h2 class=3D"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id=3D"contact">Contact<a h=
ref=3D"https://jan.ai/about/#contact" class=3D"hash-link" aria-label=3D"Dir=
ect link to Contact" title=3D"Direct link to Contact">=E2=80=8B</a></h2>
<p>Drop us a message in our <a href=3D"https://discord.gg/af6SaTdzpx" targe=
t=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Discord</a> and we'll get back to =
you.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>#general</code>: for general discussion</li>
<li><code>#get-help</code>: for bug reports and troubleshooting</li>
<li><code>#roadmap</code>: for feature requests and ideas</li>
</ul>
